The torturous tenderness I had always felt for Annette gained newpoignancy from my feelings for our little child (I "trembled" over her asNinella put it in her coarse Russian, complaining it might be bad for thebaby, even if one "subtracted the overacting"). That was the human side ofour marriage. The sexual side disintegrated altog